==Turkish==
===Etynology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[مرحبا]]}} (marħába), [[welcome]], < the root verb {{ARchar|[[رحب]]}} (ráħiba), to be wide, and {{ARchar|[[رحب]]}} (ráħħaba), to make welcome, to receive graciously.

===Interjection===
'''merhaba'''

# [[hello]], [[hi]]

